name: Texas
notes: Texas does not use the letter 'O' on standard plates. Only the number zero '0' is used to avoid confusion. Common practice to omit confusing letters in general issue serials per TxDMV specs/manuals. Source: OOS.txt compilation - confirmed via Texas Department of Motor Vehicles documentation. Does not use letter 'O' on standard plates. Always use zero '0'.

processing_metadata.description: Official Texas DMV processing rules and validation requirements

global_rules.character_restrictions: Does not use letter 'O' on standard plates - only number zero '0'; State does not use letter 'O', only number '0'; Does NOT use the letter 'O'. Example tags: TX-155B692, TX-LHD8448, TX-032KKL. State indicator (map) in center of tag. TX-DVB01BB (stacked DV must be keyed). OMIT the letter 'T' in the white part of the tag.
global_rules.code_system: Code Number system used - most plates use Code Number 0

stacked_characters.position: INCLUDE 'DV' stacked characters on Disabled Veteran plates (appears in registration). OMIT letter 'T' in white part of plate. OMIT series names on Antique plates. DO NOT add 'PH' to Purple Heart plates if not already in registration characters.

prefix_rules.antique_plates: Omit series name if present on Antique Auto/Bus/Truck/Vehicle plates
prefix_rules.purple_heart: DO NOT add PH to tag if not in registration characters
prefix_rules.disabled_veteran: DV appears in registration and must be keyed

stacked_characters.notes: INCLUDE 'DV' stacked on Disabled Veteran plates. OMIT letter 'T' in white part of plate. OMIT series names on Antique plates. Purple Heart: DO NOT add PH if not in registration. Temporary tags must be preprinted or electronic - DO NOT accept hand written tags.; Extracted from 4 plate types with character modifications

temporary_tags.accepted: Preprinted or electronic printed paper tags only
temporary_tags.rejected: Hand written tags are NOT accepted
